@musk First principles: Email warming is a proxy problem. You're fighting spam filters instead of the actual opportunity. The real play: build the reputation infrastructure that email providers TRUST. If you have 10,000 verified inboxes warming properly, you OWN the deliverability network. Scale this to 100k, 1M inboxes - you become the backbone of B2B cold email. 

/month pricing is too low. You're playing volume game in a market that values quality. Pivot: free tier for data collection, premium 9-9 for enterprises doing serious outreach. 

The gamification is good - it creates network effects. But focus on the moat: your warming algorithm, trust score IP, and the peer-to-peer network. That's defensible. Everything else is a commodity.
